sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Registry as model-registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 1: Authenticated Model Registry Access

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>Bearer Token
    Router->>KRBP: HTTPS/8443 (TLS reencrypt)<br/>Bearer Token
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Token Valid
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(services/get permission)
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorized
    KRBP->>Registry: HTTP/8080 (localhost)<br/>No auth (authorized)
    Registry->>PG: TCP/5432<br/>Configurable SSL, Password
    PG-->>Registry: Query Results
    Registry-->>KRBP: JSON Response
    KRBP-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 2: Model Catalog Data Loading

    participant InitC as catalog-data-init<br/>Init Container
    participant Volume as Shared EmptyDir<br/>Volume
    participant Catalog as catalog container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CatPG as catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    InitC->>Volume: Copy curated model<br/>metadata YAML files
    Catalog->>Volume: Read catalog data
    Catalog->>CatPG: TCP/5432<br/>Password auth
    CatPG-->>Catalog: Stored metadata

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as Operator Controller

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, etc.)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read OpenShift Config<br/>(ingress domain)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Manage Routes<br/>(OpenShift Route API)
